<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	Author(s). (Year of publication). <em>Title of report</em> (Report No. or additional 
	information about report). Publisher.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<span class="hover" title="Author(s)">Smith, A., &amp; Brown, J.</span> 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2011</span>). 
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of report">Learning opportunities in cyberspace: A report on new technologies</span></em>
	(<span class="hover" title="Report No. or additional information about report">Research Report No. 24</span>). 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">University of Western Sydney, Centre for Education Research</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
The name of the university is usually the publisher. If the report was published by a department within 
the university, include the university name followed by the name of the department. For online reports, 
add the URL at the end of the reference. The URL is displayed as a hyperlink. 
